commit.message: Treat method references like the equivalent lambda.
Fix bug where initializers could generate duplicate warnings.
Add ThisEscape.html doc note and link the new @implNote's to it.
Display all initializer warnings instead of just the first.
Add back -Werror to javac flags, reverting temporary commit 800d7344.
Add @implNote's to some popular classes that leak 'this' during construction.
Add more @SuppressWarnings("this-escape") now required after recent fixes.
Add a unit test that verifies unqualified method invocations.
Reverse the order in which the warnings show a leak's "stack trace".
Fix bug when checking subtypes: need to erase first.
Recognize that local classes cannot be externally extended.
Add some additional notes & comments on algorithm.
Add missing check for unqualified non-static method invocations.
Temporary commit: Remove -Werror from javac flags.
Temporary commit: Add -Xmaxwarns 10000 to javac flags.
Update unit test expected output after source file edits.
Add some @SuppressWarnings("this-escape") missed in previous commit.
Suppress 'this' escape warnings using @SuppressAnnotations instead of build flags.

Eliminate duplicate 'this' escape warnings.

Warning B duplicates warning A if the stack trace of A is a prefix of
the stack trace of B. For example, if constructor Foo(int x) has a
leak, and constructor Foo() invokes this(0), then emitting a warning
for Foo() would be redundant.
No 'this' escape possible from sealed class with zero permits.
